narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Great advanced level design course thought creation of design in the context of both design history and design industry.
I learned the history of design and how to design a successful book.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The history lectures and the book project (second half) were excellent and thought a lot about design as a historical practice and design as manufacture.

Doug's portion of the class was incredible. Doug is amazing and his overview of the history of design was so valuable to my education. Julian's half of class always went over time and could have been better if split the same way as Doug.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! But would recommend a typography course (at least) before taking.
The class really helps you become a better designer. Doug's lectures on the history of design are incredibly valuable.
